In article <CtMA48.KFz@efn.org>, Britt Green <brittg@efn.org> wrote:
)
)	In my readings, I've often run across the phrase "one time pad", 
)but it's never explained.  Just what _is_ a one time pad?
)
)	Thanks,
)
)	--Britt

It's an encryption system in which a different unique key is used to
encrypt each message. At one time (pun intended) they were put in pads
of paper. As each key was used, the paper was torn off the pad and
destroyed.

Mike
